# Zapatismo â€“ Steering Rule

Use this as the steering context for every chat. Full details: `.docs/system/project-rules.md`, `.docs/system/setup-architecture.md`.

## Principles

- **Simplicity first.** Boring, well-understood solutions over novel ones. Explicit over implicit; no magic.
- **Repository is source of truth.** Architecture, migrations, and API contract are version-controlled in the repo.
- **Stateless backend.** No in-memory session or app state; persistence only in the database.
- **No manual production changes.** Schema, config, and deployment must be automated (CI/CD, migrations, env vars).

## Stack & Structure

- **3-tier:** Angular frontend â†’ NestJS backend (REST API) â†’ MySQL. All run in Docker locally.
- **Workout data source:** **Strava API**. Workouts are synced from Strava via the backend (no native iOS app). See `.docs/system/research-strava-api.md`.
- **Monorepo:** `apps/backend`, `apps/frontend`, `packages/`, `prisma/`, `.docs/system/`.
- **Tooling:** Prisma Migrate for schema, OpenAPI for API contract, Docker for runtimes (backend/frontend).

## Conventions to Enforce

| Area | Rule |
|------|------|
| **Migrations** | Prisma Migrate only. Edit `schema.prisma` â†’ `npx prisma migrate dev --name <description>` â†’ commit. No manual SQL on prod; no edits to applied migrations. Test migrations (`prisma/test-migrations/`) are data-only, dev/stage only. |
| **Backend** | Stateless; DTOs for all public API (no exposing Prisma models); validation at boundary; OpenAPI in sync; no business logic in controllers. TypeScript strict. |
| **Frontend** | REST API only; no business logic duplication; typed clients from OpenAPI; UI/UX logic only. Styling: **Tailwind CSS** with **daisyUI**. |
| **Workout sync** | Strava API integration in backend; OAuth and token storage server-side; idempotent import by external activity ID. See .docs/system/research-strava-api.md. |
| **API** | OpenAPI is the contract; version-controlled; no persistence details in responses; prefer additive changes. |
| **Repo** | Branch from `development`; PR into `development` required before merge. No secrets in repo; use `.env` and `.env.development`. |
| **Docker** | One-command startup (DB + migrations + backend + frontend). Env-based config; no hardcoded prod values. |
| **Security** | Secrets in environment only; no PII/credentials in logs; keep deps updated. |

## Non-Goals

- No microservices, no premature event-driven or CQRS, no frontend business logic, no ORM magic without migration traceability.

When in doubt: prefer simpler, explicit, and consistent with the docs above.
